76561198031531253,Not Recommended,427810,20939977,"Posted: 3 February, 2016",all,Hopefullylesspretentious,"This is basically the Inception of video games. So complicated and weird that your initial response is to think it must be good, because ultimately it's too weird for you to figure out. So we pretend we understand, and that we all like it, in an attempt to appear intelligent. The truth, though, is that the game is empty of meaning; that it just avoids having any substance in favor of confusing you so much that you think it does have something to it. It really, really, doesn't. There's going to be discussion of this game the same way there was discussion of Inception, people arguing about wha♥♥♥♥♥meant, and what the ending actually is. It's not really anything. I will say the puzzles were superb, but all of the buildup with plot and atmosphere were meaningless, in the end. If you like puzzles, go for it, but if you'll get invested in trying ot figure out what's going on, take a pass on this one."
