76561198229231924,Not Recommended,427810,30352864,Posted: 6 March,all,teufel_barde,"Calendula is a very short puzzle game with the concept revolving around a game that does not want to be played. in a similar vein to pony island or other such titles.Calendula was, for me, not a worth while experience. I beat the entire game in under an hour and was rather disappointed with the experience overall. There is no plot to speak of besides the game not wanting to be played and requiring you to solve about 8 puzzles, all of which take little time to solve once you read the clues given at the start of each ""section"" by hovering over the black eye. Most of your time will be spent pressing the W key to move forward in what might as well have been cutscenes.Each puzzle requires you to mess with the settings of the game or to just witness an odd event within the menu screen in order to progress, some of these puzzles are interesting, but none of them require too much thought to solve. The only good things i have to say about the game are that its music is pleasent, the style of everything is forboding and unique, and that it did manage to generate the feeling of not being able to play a game because the settings were off: irritation and boredom.Overall Calendula is a simple puzzle game with a weird, vague ""arthouse"" style of doing things. Its short, easy, disinteresting and overall not worth buying at full price, If even half price, as there are far better puzzle games with better stories that you can buy for around the same price and get much more for your money (puzzle agent for example)."
