76561198094608127,Not Recommended,427810,26343738,"Posted: 31 October, 2016",all,triesleast,"After watching the trailer for this game, I got pretty hyped, expecting it to break the 4th wall a ton, have interesting puzzles with clever solutions, and a meaningful mix of puzzles and first person exploration used to tell some chilling story/have a spooky revelation. Instead, I got barely 30 mins of playtime where I was mostly stuck on the main menu, solving very easy puzzles that mostly revolved around changing settings and clicking play. The walking segments were basically on rails: you have no control over direction you walk, cannot move the camera enough to take in anything besides that which is in front of you, and end with a cutscene of raw meat. The story was all but nonexistant, and felt like the bones of meaning were just there to give some semblance of purpose for the player to make them continue the game. I never felt ""spooked"" by this game, or intruiged. There were no elements present that haven't been done better in a different game, and I felt robbed not only by the lack of content, but also by the large claims the store page for it made, but failed to back up. Every single part of the game, save the only real attempt at breaking the 4th wall at the end, is shown in the trailer. I cannot reccomend this game when I have played flash games for free with more content, more clever puzzles, better use of the 4th wall, and backed up content claims."
