76561198271366847,Recommended,427810,23262484,"Posted: 28 May, 2016",all,Rachel,"You'll find yourself reminded a lot of Pony Island while playing this game.  It leans heavily on inspiration into the world of metaphysics, and you find yourself questioning whether Calendula is a malevolent or benevolent entitiy.  The puzzles were clever, and I enjoyed the unsettling atmosphere.  It will take you about 50 minutes to play through the entire thing, so I definitely wouldn't say it's worth $7, but it's a great experience.  The ending will have you thrown.  The entire point of the game is definitely unclear, and the ""cutscenes"" (points in the game in which you simply move forward through rooms) seem to be unconnected, but the atmosphere gives me shivers.Less of a game, more of an experience that you interact with.  However, that is definitely not a bad thing."
