,Recommended,427810,32615665,Posted: 21 June,all,One Step Ahead Delcat,"This does an excellent job of doing a lot with a little, creating an unsettling and oppressive atmosphere with minimal assets.  For best results, go in completely blind.  Don't even look at the screenshots, seriously.  For REALLY best results, don't go in expecting Pony Island.  Pony Island is great, but Calendula is its own experience.That having been said, the game IS short, and I say that as someone who loves short games.  I wanted more because I was thoroughly enjoying myself, and I hope the devs will continue their good work--I'd love to see a more full-fledged game.  While I've played worse for more money, I wouldn't shy away from a Steam sale for this one.NOTE: This game features a LOT of flashing lights and quick frame changes.  Please be aware if you're susceptible to such things."
